==English==

===Noun===
'''prop'''  (''plural:'' '''[[props]]''')
# An [[item]] placed on a [[stage]] to create a [[scene]] or scenario in which [[actor]]s perform a [[play]] in a [[theatre]] or [[motion picture]].  Usually the term "props" is reserved for [[object]]s with which an actor interacts (e.g. a [[glass]], a [[book]] or a [[weapon]]).  Larger items adding to the scene, (e.g. [[chair]]s) are considered part of the [[set]].
# An object [[placed]] against or under another, to [[support]] it; anything that supports
# {{rugby}}: The player who is next to the [[hooker]] in a [[scrum]].
# The [[propeller]] of an [[aircraft]]

===Transitive verb===
'''to prop'''
# to support or [[shore up]] something

===Related terms===
*[[warm props]] - [[extra]]s or people with non-speaking roles usually used to make a scene look more realistic.

